access: The entire vacation apartment is yours!  You have exclusive access to all of it including the balcony area. Make yourself at home! ;)
additional_house_rules:
- No smoking indoors.  We take pride in our home and the first impression that our guests experience when they walk in the door.  Cigarette odors are hard to get rid of so we ask that you smoke outdoors so we can maintain the fresh, clean smell of our home for all of our guests.  
-Absolutely No parties my landlord is also my neighbor and if you have a party in my apartment you will cause serious problems for me. If you have a party int he apartment we will ask you to find other accomodations. 
- Please return all sets of keys at the end of your stay.  Otherwise you will be charged a $60.00 fee as we would be forced to replace the locks the doors. 

Checking in: 
Check-in time is 4pm.

Early check-ins:
Please keep in mind that if you wish to check in early and we have guests checking out the same morning, we will need to give our cleaning staff enough time to prepare the apartment for you.  We may not always be able to check you in early, but notifying us as soon as you know that you may need an early check-in will ensure that we accommodate you to the best of our ability.  If we're not able to check you in early, we would be more than happy to hold your luggage until the apartment is clean and ready for check-in. 

Checking out:
Check-out is at 12pm.

Late check-outs:
The check out time is set to give us enough time to prepare the apartment for guests that may be checking in that afternoon.  If there are no guests checking in that afternoon, we are always more than happy to extend the check-out time for your as late as we can.  We do ask that you notify us at least 48 hours in advance should you need a late check-out and we will do our best to accommodate you.  Please be advised that late checkout fees may apply.

- We ask that you close all the windows when you leave the apartment.  We take pride in our original hardwood floors and if it happens to rain after you leave, the water will severely damage the floors and window sills.

- Please make sure you have all of your belongings before checking out.  If you do leave something behind, let us know right away and we'll do our best to find it and ship it to you.  We are not responsible for lost items.

- Access to the roof is RESTRICTED.  Not only is it unsafe for our guests to be on the roof, it is against the law.

- We've invested a lot of time and care into making sure the apartment is your home away from home when you visit.  Most things in the apartment are new and our cleaning staff goes over the entire apartment before someone checks in and after someone checks out.  If you notice anything broken or damaged upon your arrival, please notify us immediately to ensure you are not held accountable for it.

- We know accidents do happen.  If you break or damage anything in the apartment during your stay, please notify us right away so we can handle it accordingly. 

We provide quality linens for your comfort during your stay.  However, we ask that you DO NOT take any of these items with you.  We charge the following fees for any linens that are missing upon check-out: 
$30 per towel
$45 per bed sheet or similar linens
$100 per comforter
$30 per pillow

As always, honesty and kindness are always the best policies.  

We hope you have a wonderful stay in this big, beautiful city!

- Absolutely NO PETS allowed.  We love animals but some people are highly allergic and this can pose a serious issue with other guests.  In the event this rule is broken, a $500.00 fine will be imposed.
We look forward to hosting you!

~Bianca & Meli
description:
Our place is close to Manhattan and all the main attractions in NYC! As well as John Brown Smokehouse, Monika's Cafe Bar, Kaufman Astoria Studios, Malagueta Restaurant, and Napoli Pizza & Pasta. You’ll love the place because of the comfortable beds, the kitchen, and the hominess. It's great for couples, solo adventurers, business travelers, families (with kids), and larger groups.

This two bedroom apartment (not including the living room! which makes it a nice three bedroom) features brand new, cozy and comfortable furniture.  This is a first-floor apartment, with a porch and lots of sunlight.  Let's talk about the accommodations: 

Living room: Full-sized sofa bed
Bedroom 1: Queen size bed and a single size futon
Bedroom 2: Full-sized bed

The entire vacation apartment is yours!  You have exclusive access to all of it including the balcony area. Make yourself at home! ;)

We understand and respect your privacy, and we are aware that your stay may be short.  We leave it entirely up to our guests to decide how much communication they feel comfortable having with their host. Feel free to reach out to us!

You'll find plenty to do in Astoria and Long Island City.  They are great neighborhoods and extremely safe both in the day and at night.  More importantly, it's so close to Midtown Manhattan! The city obviously speaks for itself but you're about 30 minutes away (by train, by cab is even faster!) from Times Square, Midtown and Central Park!

In the neighborhood, you'll find a pizza shop for those late night snacks right downstairs.  Just a 2-minute walk to supermarkets, grocery stores, restaurants, bars, shopping and more! There's a playground and park two blocks away.  

We've set up a guidebook with our favorite places in the area.  You can find it in your booking.  

If you're coming with a car, please keep in mind that this is New York City and that means you'll need to find street parking.  It is very safe to park on the street in this neighborhood as well, so no worries!

The apartment is located near the N and Q trains which will take you to Midtown Manhattan in about 10 minutes (3 stops) and Central Park (4 stops).  The train station is 2 short blocks away.  It is also very easy and inexpensive to catch a cab into Manhattan if you prefer.  We've left subway and bus maps in the apartment for your convenience.
